<h1>Fahrenheit to Kelvin</h1>
<p>Fahrenheit to Kelvin conversion is done by using a simple formula i.e. (=
T)<sub>K</sub> =3D 5/9 (T)<sub>F</sub> + 459.67. Fahrenheit and Kelvin are =
the two very commonly known and used scales for temperature. While the Fahr=
enheit scale of temperature is used in the United States, the Kelvin scale =
is used extensively for scientific calculations worldwide. There is a lot o=
f scientific and engineering equipment that makes use of the Fahrenheit sca=
le. Let us see learn the Fahrenheit to Kelvin formula along with a few solv=
ed examples.</p>
