<p>T<sub>F</sub> =3D 0=C2=BA F(Given)</p>
<p>Using F to K formula,</p>
<p>(T)<sub>K</sub> =3D 5/9 [(T)<sub>F</sub><sub> </sub>+ 459.67]</p>
<p>Putting the value:</p>
<p>=3D 5/9(0=C2=BA+459.67)</p>
<p>=3D 5/9(459.67)</p>
<p>=3D 2298.35/9</p>
<p><strong>=3D </strong>255.37 K</p>
<p>Therefore,<b> </b>0 degree Fahrenheit =3D 255.37 K</p>
</div>
